      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is stupid Go gotcha: https://github.com/golang/go/wiki/CommonMistakes#using-goroutines-on-loop-iterator-variables\n\nBasically, without this line the function on line 84 captures \u0027prop\u0027 variable that lives outside the loop. So all funcs will reference same variable (that eventually will just contain the last props.Prop). \u0027prop :\u003d prop\u0027 line defines \u0027prop\u0027 in a loop body scope, so each \u0027func\u0027 gets a closure around its own copy of \u0027prop\u0027 variable.",
